FT  30 JUL 94 / UK Company News: John Lusty
John Lusty Group, the USM-quoted food importer, reported reduced pre-tax
losses of Pounds 633,000 for the 14 months to January 31, against Pounds
2.25m for the previous 12 months.
Turnover was Pounds 8.65m (Pounds 8.68m) of which Pounds 404,000 (Pounds
740,000) related to discontinued activities and Pounds 1.48m to
acquisitions. Operating losses were Pounds 513,000 (Pounds 1.93m) with
Pounds 40,000 (Pounds 52,000) from discontinued activities. Acquisitions
contributed profits of Pounds 113,000.
Losses per share were 1.46p (19.38p).
